    '2020': "SECTION B  (100 MARKS) \nQuestions must be answered in th e language indicated on the exa mination paper.  \n L A  M O D A  R Á P I D A  \nQ. 1  5  × 3 marks = 15 marks\n[If extra words are added or words are omitted no marks will be  awarded] \n(a) quizás                 (3m)\n(b) salario justo                 (3m)\n(c) adquirió  unos     (3m)\n(d) los estudiantes pro ponen        (3m)\n(e) planean establecer (3m)  \nQ. 2 \n 3 × 5 marks = 15 marks\n(a)… we wonder/ask ourselves about the negative impact….          (5m)\n(b) ... the quantities of water n eeded are immense....                 (5m)\n(c)… (they) carried out a study to investigate…     (5m)\nQ. 3  5 × 1 mark = 5 marks\n[If extra words are added or words are omitted no marks will be  awarded] \n(a) precio               (1m)\n(b) peligro                (1m)\n(c) por eso (1m)\n(d) manera               (1m) \n(e) solucionan      (1m) \nQ. 4  (2+2+1 marks) + (2+2+1 m arks) + (5 marks) = 15 marks\n[In (a) and (b) the first two correct answers = 2+2m, the third  answer =1m] \n(a)-     they wor\nk long days\n- for low wages\n- in unhealthy conditi ons (2+2+1m)\n(b) -     to find ways to generate awareness\n-about the consumption of fast fashion\n-and its impact on the p lanet (2+2+1m)  \n(c)One of:\n-To buy less [2m], we all have a l ot of clothes that we don’t us e [2m];\nwe should always consider if we really need that shirt/ item [1m]\n-Buy intelligently [2m], quality brands that last [3m]\n-Don’t throw clothing in the rubbish [2m] sell it [2m] or recycl e it [1m] (5m)       \n\n11           Section B: Question 5          TOTAL MARKS: 50 \n     Guidelines for Marking Question 5 (Linked Question) \n1. CONTENT/COMMUNI CATION 25 marks         \nTOP               \nHigh level of coherence \nClear argumentation \nCommunicative intention fulfilled \nLittle or no irrelevant  material 18 – 25 marks \nMIDDLE        \nReasonable level of coherence \nComprehensible to Spanish speaker \nCommunicative intention more or less respected \nSome irrelevant mater ial 9 – 17 marks \nBOTTOM         \nLack of coherence \nSpanish speaker would have difficulty understanding \nCommunicative intention not fulfilled \nA lot of irrelevant material                0 – 8 marks \n2. LANGUAGE  \n25 marks \nTOP \nIdiomatic Spanish \nGood level of vocabulary \nFew grammatical/spelling mistakes  \nCorrect usage of tenses 18 – 25 marks \nMIDDLE \nVocabulary quite good - general ly adequate and appropriate  \nVerbs generally correct \nNot too many spelling/gra mmatical mistakes 9 – 17 marks \nBOTTOM \nProblems with vocabulary – limited range of vocabulary \nMost verbs incorrect \nMany spelling mistakes 0 – 8 marks \nNote:  \nWhere no marks are awarded for Content, (i.e. effort totally i rrelevant), no marks will be \nawarded for Language. \nNo marks will be awarded for phrases taken directly from the article.  \n\n12 SECTION C     (50 MARKS)  \nCandidates are required to attempt  either  1 (a) or 1 (b) AND either 2 (a) or 2 (b) \nGuidelines for Section C \n•Should a candidate answer parts (a) and (b) of Question 1 or Question 2 in error, both  must be\nmarked and marks awarded only for the higher scoring of the two.\n•Minor inaccuracies (i.e. which do not distort ‘message’) should  be ignored.\n•Verbs must be correct for full marks.\nNote:       In any part of written production the same mistakes will not be penalised twice. \nQuestion 1. When marking this question – either (a) or (b) – the priorities indicated for Content and Language in Section B, Q.5.should be broadly adhered to. \nQuestion 1 (a)  DIALOGUE CONSTRUCTION \nFive ‘turns’.  Allow a maximum of 6 marks each.  (30 marks)\n(5 x 6m = 30 marks) \nOR \nQuestion 1 (b) \nLETTER / EMAIL (30 marks) \n•There are five points to be made.  Allow a maximum of 6 marks each.        (5 x 6m = 30 marks)\n•Note that each point should be developed and expanded.\n•Letter/email can be loosely based on the suggestions given.\n•Candidates can make their own points and need not use the guide lines given.\n•Correct register for le tter/email is expected.\nCriteri",
